isCollateralized(bytes32,address).details: Return if the borrowing power for a given collateral of an user is equal or greater than its debt for the same collateral

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

post(bytes32,address,address,uint256).details: Takes collateral _token from `from` address, and credits it to `to` collateral account.

powerOf(bytes32,address).details: Maximum borrowing power of an user in dai for a given collateral

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

repayDai(bytes32,uint256,address,uint256.details: Takes dai from `from` address, user debt is decreased for the given collateral and yDai series.

repayYDai(bytes32,uint256,address,uint25.details: Burns yDai of a given series from `from` address, user debt is decreased for the given collateral and yDai series.

revokeAccess(address).details: Remove user to the authorized users list

revokeProxy(address).details: Stop a proxy from acting on the behalf of caller

shutdown().details: Disables post, withdraw, borrow and repay. To be called only by shutdown management contracts.

systemDebt().details: Returns the total debt of the yDai system, across all series, in dai

totalDebtDai(bytes32,address).details: Returns the total debt of an user, for a given collateral, across all series, in Dai

totalDebtYDai(bytes32,address).details: Returns the total debt of an user, for a given collateral, across all series, in yDai

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(bytes32,address,address,uint256.details: Returns collateral to `to` address, taking it from `from` collateral account.
